# Case B: Music Studio Infrastructure

## Client
Mr. O'Neal, Music Teacher

## Problem
Lesson materials and student progress data are scattered. No centralized system tracks repertoire, skill levels, or goals.

## Goal
Build a Music Student Profile system as a three-stage pipeline: Google Form -> Google Sheet -> Interactive Website. Each form submission logs as a new timestamped row; the website displays each student's most recent profile plus history.

## Tech Stack
Google Forms, Google Sheets, Google Apps Script, JavaScript/HTML/CSS for the website

## Team
Developers: Serena Zhang, JT Gannon
Club Lead: Cayden Auyang

## Working Rules
- This folder is scoped to Case B only. Do not modify files outside projects/case-b-music-studio/ unless explicitly asked.
- Do not commit secrets, API keys, or credentials. Use .env files and add them to .gitignore.
- Follow the club branch naming convention: case-b/short-description (lowercase, hyphens).
- Never push directly to main. All changes go through a Pull Request with at least 1 approval.
- When writing code, prefer clarity over cleverness. These developers are high school students learning collaborative coding.
- If you generate code the developer cannot explain, flag it and summarize what it does in plain English.

## Definition of Done (Phase 1)
Working Google Form linked to a Google Sheet with defined fields, plus a static website prototype displaying a mock student profile.
